==English==
===Etymology===
From the distance travelled by a taxicab in a grid of streets that cross at right angles to each other

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[taxicab]] [[geometry]]''' (''[[uncountable]]'')
#{{geometry}} A [[non-Euclidean geometry]] in which the [[distance]] between two [[point]]s is the [[sum]] of the [[absolute]] [[difference]]s between their corresponding [[coordinate]]s.